abstract: South Africa seamer Vernon Philander has announced he will retire from all forms of international cricket after the four-match test series against England starting on Thursday.
snippet: South Africa seamer Vernon Philander has announced he will retire from all forms of international cricket after the four-match test series against England starting on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: PRETORIA — South Africa seamer Vernon Philander has announced he will retire from all forms of international cricket after the four-match test series against England starting on Thursday.
headline_main: South Africa's Philander to Retire After England Test Series
headline_print_headline: South Africa's Philander to Retire After England Test Series

abstract: Authorities searched Monday for four Chinese crew members who were taken hostage by pirates in speedboats off Gabon's capital over the weekend.
snippet: Authorities searched Monday for four Chinese crew members who were taken hostage by pirates in speedboats off Gabon's capital over the weekend.
lead_paragraph: LIBREVILLE, Gabon — Authorities searched Monday for four Chinese crew members who were taken hostage by pirates in speedboats off Gabon's capital over the weekend.
headline_main: 1 Killed, 4 Chinese Abducted as Pirates Attack Ship in Gabon
headline_print_headline: 1 Killed, 4 Chinese Abducted as Pirates Attack Ship in Gabon

abstract: The venture capital arm of Sweden's Norrsken Foundation has raised 61 million euros ($68 million) towards the 100 million it hopes to gather for a new impact fund, an investment vehicle that aims to provide environmental and social benefits as well as financial returns.
snippet: The venture capital arm of Sweden's Norrsken Foundation has raised 61 million euros ($68 million) towards the 100 million it hopes to gather for a new impact fund, an investment vehicle that aims to provide environmental and social benefits as wel...
lead_paragraph: STOCKHOLM — The venture capital arm of Sweden's Norrsken Foundation has raised 61 million euros ($68 million) towards the 100 million it hopes to gather for a new impact fund, an investment vehicle that aims to provide environmental and social benefits as well as financial returns.
headline_main: New Swedish Impact Fund Raises 61 Million Euro, Targets 100 Million
headline_print_headline: New Swedish Impact Fund Raises 61 Million Euro, Targets 100 Million

abstract: Thousands of Indians have been protesting against a new citizenship law as well as possible plans for a National Register of Citizens (NRC), alleging the measures are an attack on a secular constitution and against minority Muslims.
snippet: Thousands of Indians have been protesting against a new citizenship law as well as possible plans for a National Register of Citizens (NRC), alleging the measures are an attack on a secular constitution and against minority Muslims.
lead_paragraph: MUMBAI — Thousands of Indians have been protesting against a new citizenship law as well as possible plans for a National Register of Citizens (NRC), alleging the measures are an attack on a secular constitution and against minority Muslims.
headline_main: Explainer: Why India's New Citizenship Plans Are Stirring Protests
headline_print_headline: Explainer: Why India's New Citizenship Plans Are Stirring Protests

abstract: Russia's Rosneft and Norway's Equinor have agreed details on how to develop an Arctic Siberian onshore oilfield, they said on Monday, their first joint investment since agreeing a strategic partnership in 2012.
snippet: Russia's Rosneft and Norway's Equinor have agreed details on how to develop an Arctic Siberian onshore oilfield, they said on Monday, their first joint investment since agreeing a strategic partnership in 2012.
lead_paragraph: OSLO/MOSCOW — Russia's Rosneft and Norway's Equinor have agreed details on how to develop an Arctic Siberian onshore oilfield, they said on Monday, their first joint investment since agreeing a strategic partnership in 2012.
headline_main: Equinor, Rosneft to Develop Arctic Oilfield in Joint Investment
headline_print_headline: Equinor, Rosneft to Develop Arctic Oilfield in Joint Investment

abstract: Saudi Arabia has been accused of shielding Prince Mohammed bin Salman, who foreign experts suspect was behind the killing of Jamal Khashoggi.
snippet: Saudi Arabia has been accused of shielding Prince Mohammed bin Salman, who foreign experts suspect was behind the killing of Jamal Khashoggi.
lead_paragraph: BEIRUT, Lebanon — A court in Saudi Arabia sentenced five men to death and three to prison terms over the killing of the Saudi dissident writer Jamal Khashoggi in Istanbul last year, the kingdom’s public prosecutor said on Monday.

abstract: Uzbekistan's Liberal Democratic Party have retained the biggest number of seats in the Central Asian nation's legislature so far, winning 43 seats out of 128 in Sunday's vote which Western monitors criticised for "numerous serious irregularities".
snippet: Uzbekistan's Liberal Democratic Party have retained the biggest number of seats in the Central Asian nation's legislature so far, winning 43 seats out of 128 in Sunday's vote which Western monitors criticised for "numerous serious irregularities".
lead_paragraph: TASHKENT — Uzbekistan's Liberal Democratic Party have retained the biggest number of seats in the Central Asian nation's legislature so far, winning 43 seats out of 128 in Sunday's vote which Western monitors criticised for "numerous serious irregularities".
headline_main: Uzbekistan's LibDems Lead in Vote Criticised by Western Observers

abstract: Algerian President Abdelmadjid Tebboune has appointed General Said Chengriha as the acting head of the armed forces after the death of Lieutenant General Ahmed Gaed Saleh, the presidency said on Monday.
snippet: Algerian President Abdelmadjid Tebboune has appointed General Said Chengriha as the acting head of the armed forces after the death of Lieutenant General Ahmed Gaed Saleh, the presidency said on Monday.
lead_paragraph: ALGIERS — Algerian President Abdelmadjid Tebboune has appointed General Said Chengriha as the acting head of the armed forces after the death of Lieutenant General Ahmed Gaed Saleh, the presidency said on Monday.
headline_main: Algeria's President Appoints General Said Chengriha as Acting Army Chief
